hints.description: This company provides human capital management (HCM) software and services, helping businesses manage their workforce from recruitment to retirement. Their cloud-based platform offers solutions for payroll, benefits administration, talent management, and workforce management, catering to mid-sized and large enterprises. CEO Jim ****** has been instrumental in driving the company's growth and expansion within the competitive HCM market.
hints.funFact1: Initially founded in 1999 as a provider of payroll services, the company underwent a significant transformation in the mid-2000s, pivoting to a broader HCM software platform and rebranding to its current name.
hints.funFact2: The company's name is derived from the concept of "dayforce," representing the continuous flow of information and processes needed to manage a modern workforce, emphasizing its commitment to real-time data and operational efficiency.
